Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1; ruled lines: 17; written lines: 17; Uniform layout. Visible hard-point ruling. Hair side and flesh side of folios distinguishable. Titles and inital words in larger square characters. Last word of a quire repeated at the beginning of a new quire. Marginal notes. Unfoliated blank leaf after folio 105.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Sefardi semi-cursive and square script, punctuated, of the 15th century.

binding.p: BM/BL in-house. Spine: 'Hebrew Grammar. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Additional Ms. 18,970.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: Adolphus Asher (b. 1800, d. 1853), Berlin bookseller and dealer to the British Museum 1841-1853: purchased by the British Museum from him on 12 June 1852: inscribed, folio [126v] (fse001v).
